nges noted. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying isn\'t transformed. It reverts to its true form if it dies. <br><br><strong>Devil\'s Sight.</strong> Magical darkness doesn\'t impede the imp\'s darkvision. <br><br><strong>Magic Resistance.</strong> The imp has advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects.','Tiny Fiend','dungeon,planar','[{ \"name\": \"Deception\", \"bonus\": \"4\"},{ \"name\": \"Insight\", \"bonus\": \"3\"},{ \"name\": \"Persuasion\", \"bonus\": \"4\"},{ \"name\": \"Stealth\", \"bonus\": \"5\"}]',NULL,'[]','[{\"name\": \"Sting\", \"bonus\": \"5\", \"damage\": \"1d4+3 pierce damage, and the target must make on a DC 11 Constitution saving throw, taking 3d6 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.\", \"special\": null},{\"name\": \"Invisibility\", \"bonus\": null, \"damage\": \"<strong>Invisibility.</strong> The imp magically turns invi sib le until it attacks or until its concentration ends (as if concentrating on a spell). Any equipment the imp wears or carries is invisible with it.\", \"special\": null}]','Imp.jpg',1,969),('Giant octopus','326','1',NULL,'10ft. swim 60ft','11',NULL,'8d10+8',1,3,1,1,-3,0,-3,3,1,1,-3,0,-3,'darkvision 60ft., passive Perception 14','<strong>Hold Breath</strong> While out of water the octopus can hold it\'s breath for 1 hour. <br><br><strong>Underwater Camouplage</strong> The octopus has advantage on Dexterity (stealth) checks made while underwater. <br><br><strong>Water Breathing</strong> the octopus can breath only underwater.','Large Beast','aquatic','[{ \"name\": \"Perception\", \"bonus\": \"4\"},{ \"name\": \"Stealth\", \"bonus\": \"5\"}]',NULL,'[]','[{\"name\": \"Tentacles\", \"bonus\": \"5\", \"damage\": \"2d6+3 bludg\", \"special\": \"Reach 15ft., if target is a creature it is grappled (escape DC 16). Until grapple ends, the target is restrained, and the octopus can\'t use it\'s tentacles on another target.\"},{\"name\": \"Ink Cloud\", \"bonus\": null, \